properties.abstract: By way of Uetendorfberg to Wattenwil on the River Grbe. From here to the northern slopes of the Stockhorn range, with beautiful views of the Stockental valley and Bernese Alps. Riding through the Seeliswald nature reserve will take you to the Gltschbachtal valley.
properties.description:
Hilly at first, past Geistsee lake to the Grbe. Follow the river to Wattenwil and ride along the left side of the valley with scenic views of the Grbetal valley and Bernese Alps to Blumenstein. The route briefly follows the Stockental Hausweg theme trail with its well-preserved houses.

The branch-off to Blumenstein church appears at the upper edge of the village. The short but brief ascent is worthwhile  the sight of the pretty group of the church, cemetery and ancillary building are well worth the effort.

Take the main road from Pohlern to Niederstocken. Continue through the Seeliswald, a small, protected upland moor with carnivorous sundew, to the Gltschbachtal valley. At its centre you will find an attractive waterside barbecue and recreation area. The last section follows Lakes Amsoldingen and Uebeschi back to Uetendorf. The church at Amsoldingen with its (privately owned) castle is well worth a visit.
